# Token budget (always on)

When working in this repo during a constrained Cursor billing cycle:

1. Prefer **Composer 2.5-fast** for mechanical implementation.
2. Grok only **slow + low/medium**; escalate **high** only after FAIL/unsatisfactory.
3. Never pull `data/*.json`, `.venv`, or superseded design dumps into context (see `.cursorignore`).
4. Grok returns a short structured LOCK; Composer writes plans and code.
5. One slice at a time; cite `board.md` / `STATUS.md` / plan paths instead of re-pasting.

Full text: `cursor-agents-communication/token-budget-rules.md`
